  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Despite multiple credibility factors with achieved levels below required levels — including critical verification and validation gaps — the assurance level is declared High and the decision is Accepted. This package is intentionally adversarial: the declared assurance level of High is inconsistent with the structural evidence (COMPOUND-03).",
